## Component Usage Guidelines

1. **Always use shadcn UI components** instead of custom HTML elements or other UI libraries
2. **Import components** from the local components directory (typically `@/components/ui/`)
3. **Customize styling** using Tailwind CSS classes when needed
4. **Follow accessibility patterns** provided by shadcn UI components
5. **Use TypeScript properly** with component props and interfaces

## File Structure After Initialization

```
├── components/
│   └── ui/           # shadcn UI components will be installed here
├── lib/
│   └── utils.ts      # Utility functions (includes cn() helper)
└── components.json   # shadcn UI configuration
```

## Example Component Usage

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card"

export function ExampleComponent() {
  return (
    <Card className="w-full max-w-md">
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>Example Card</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Button variant="default" size="md">
          Click me
        </Button>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  )
}
```

## Important Notes

- **No other UI libraries** should be used in this project
- **Always check** if a component exists in shadcn UI before creating custom components
- **Prefer composition** over customization when building complex UI elements
- **Use the `cn()` utility** from `@/lib/utils` for conditional className merging